6 years of Ami Amalia. 
More about it on our website ❤️.

It starts with the yarn. 
It needs to be natural, free of petroleum, plastic. 
Premium quality, developed and spun by reputable, heritage mills , committed to beauty, quality, sustainability. 
Then it gets our attention, and we start our work of creating from it pieces that will showcase the yarn’ beauty, and your beauty. 
In a world where the material is the lowest cost element for the vast majority of the clothing sold, we respect too much our work, and your money, not to invest in the best yarns the money can buy. 
The yarns  are 100% biodegradable, but before that, the garments we knit from them can be enjoyed for many generations. 
#AmiAmalia

One of the items we selected for the 6 year event with 23% off until June 30th is our classic mariniere shirt, and we also added a few fun variations with sailing motifs - anchor, steering wheel, the boat shape. 
We also have the option to use your own motif - as we always say, take advantage while you can of having access directly to a knitting factory and its resources 🌊⛵️⚓️. 
Enjoy the softness of knitted organic cotton and the forever charm of a classic mariniere.

This jacket is my bonus choice for the 23% off, plus gift limited selection 🤍. 
My recommendation is to choose as gift from us for your order a matching bra for a wellness meets fashion meets comfort. 
Choose your favourite colours from our catalogue - this piece can be knitted from extrafine merino, or organic cotton.

Our story, our commitment to sustainability, luxury, passion for premium yarns and statement knitwear are more than words easy to use by everyone with access to internet.
What we knit for you - as much as I would like to be as easy as in the first picture :) - is made possible by our own knitwear technology, equipment, know-how, employees and close collaborators. 
#AmiAmalia

I postponed  looking at what I do through a business plan or numbers point of view as long as I could, because I knew on paper it might not make sense to put so much work and passion into it, and that my intuition of what this could become, for others, is just wishful thinking. 
Working with the Bloomberg reporter on this article took me out of that zone, as they have diligently checked every statement and wanted to see if the numbers also show that our story resonates with a niche consumer category and even asked an INSEAD professor for his view on the concept. 
“Săftoiu’s use of folk motifs turns the brand’s origin into a symbol of authenticity instead. “If you want to stand out, buying Romanian is more interesting,” Godart says.” 
Thank you for being part of our story, and here you have a glimpse also into the other aspects of the business I don’t usually talk about :)
❤️
#AmiAmalia 
Photography @andreeamacri
